Money Stuff =0A MicroStrategy Inc. is, among other things, a proof of conce=
pt. The concept =0Ais: =E2=80=9CIf you buy $100 of Bitcoin and put it in a =
pot, you can slic =0A=0A=0A <https://bloom.bg/4avGswn> =0A =0A<https://sli.=
bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12396123&m=3D21d6dea82=
d6b16615cf44233be620525&p=3D01232025>=0A=0A=0A=0AFartStrategy=0A=0AMicroStr=
ategy Inc. is, among other things, a proof of concept. The concept is: =0A=
=E2=80=9CIf you buy $100 of Bitcoin and put it in a pot, you can slice the =
pot into =0Ashares and sell them for $200.=E2=80=9D (MicroStrategy owns abo=
ut$49 billion of Bitcoin =0A<https://www.sec.gov/ix=3Fdoc=3D/Archives/edgar=
/data/1050446/000119312525009102/d853769d8k.htm>=0A and has a market capita=
lization of about $94 billion, because people will buy =0Aits shares for mo=
re than the value of the underlying Bitcoin.) This is a very =0Aappealing c=
